for infile opening ======> std::ifstream infile
for outfile opening ======> std::ofstream outfilefile

setting flags to specify different file opening modes.

we use the open() member function of the ifstream and ofstream classes. 
we pass the filename as the first argument and a set of flags as the second argument.

Here are some common flags:

std::ios::in: Open for input operations.
std::ios::out: Open for output operations.
std::ios::app: Open for appending to the end of the file.
std::ios::trunc: Truncate the file to zero length on open.
std::ios::binary: Open the file in binary mode.

example:
	std::fstream file("my_file.txt", std::ios::in | std::ios::out);